Police said the man was waiting in his car while his wife took their nine-year-old son to school. CAPE TOWN - A man has been shot dead while dropping his son at school in Port Elizabeth on Tuesday. The 43-year-old is believed to have been a local taxi boss and police suspect he was targeted. Police said the man was waiting in his car while his wife took their nine-year-old son to school. When the woman got back, two men approached the vehicle and fired shots through the driverâ€™s side. The man was shot in the head, neck and shoulder; he died on the scene. His wife was not harmed but she has been taken to a local hospital.